Sample size
The target analytic sample size is 671 participants as determined by COS power analysis.
To achieve the target analytic sample size, we anticipate the need to collect a slightly larger sample size to account for any necessary deletion due to insufficient
effort responding or extensive missing data. The target sample size for recruitment is thus 700 participants. Insufficient effort responding will be determined by
reviewing time to complete the survey: participants that complete in less than 30 seconds will be removed from the data. Participants missing more than 10% of
data per scale will have their responses removed from the data, as will participants who fail both of 2 attention check items.
Sample size rationale
Power calculations were conducted in accordance with the guidelines of the Social Sciences Replication Project (SSRP). However, instead of carrying out two
rounds of data collection to achieve the stage 1 sample size target followed by the stage 2 sample size target as in Phase 1 of SCORE, in Phase 2 only one data
collection effort will be carried out to achieve a single target analytic sample size.
All replications will aim to achieve the target analytic sample size, which is determined by a power analysis achieving 90% power to detect 50% of the original
effect size (formally referred to as the Stage 2 sample size). However, if this sample size is not attainable for the replicating lab, the sample size will instead be
calculated by achieving 90% power to detect 75% of the original effect size (formally referred to as the Stage 1 sample size).
For this study, because collecting the Stage 2 sample size would not be feasible under SCORE’s allowable budget, the Stage 1 sample size (which is powered to
detect 75% of the original effect size) will instead be collected. The Stage 1 sample size for this study is 671 participants.
Documentation of the power analysis conducted for this replication is available at the following view-only link: https://osf.io/q8xpr/?
view_only=665f77d6e7ed416fa8877edeaccdf7e3.
Stopping rule
The planned analytic sample size is 671 participants. The target sample size for recruitment is 700 participants. After achieving this sample, sampling will stop
and planned analyses will be run.
